														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2318731">
									

<p>You manage to do so many cool things with this tale. Breaking it down:</p>
<ol>
<li>You provide what is, in all honesty, a believable &quot;origin&quot; of sorts for 173 and where it comes from, as well as a &quot;cleaner&quot; version of 173's documentation and how it'd feasibly look if written today, without lessening the horror or impact of it.</li>
<li>You manage to use 2317 in a way that, while certainly questionable, is kinda unique and justifies what Multi-U is doing.</li>
<li>Your format here is awesome. Though I question how iPhone texting technology still looks the same 30 years into the future.</li>
<li>You reference Alexandra, Nala, and Moto. Niiiice.</li>
<li>If you really are planning on making this the start of something, it works perfectly as a standalone and gives me interest in what you're planning on doing.</li>
</ol>
<p>This is one of the more refreshing tales I've read on the site in a while. Have a well-deserved +1.</p>

							</div>

								
					
