														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2318750">
									

<p>Thank you for your compliments.</p>
<ol>
<li>I have to admit that &quot;redoing 173's profile&quot; was a last minute add-on after I thought about a number of failed Tales that tried something similar (present 173 via the SCP format, but &quot;updated&quot;) and flopped.</li>
<li>I will admit that 2317's use is questionable, although I wanted a end-of-the-world scenario (and I was scouting something from 2003 initially). I settled for 2317 since Clef mentioned on the KaktusKast that 2317's theme is based on Lovecraftian inevitability. I thought that it would be unique to play around that (Lovecraft never really thought of alternate realities anyway).</li>
<li>Ditto. But I was inspired by my Message app, WhatsApp and similar apps made in China, Korea and Japan.</li>
<li>Yup. Guilty as charged.</li>
<li>Yeah&#8230; based on my time in this site, I've come to realise that if one desires to attempt a series/canon, each piece must hold out on its own first.</li>
</ol>

							</div>

								
