				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/petrograd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(455145); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=455145&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610182408" alt="Petrograd" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=455145)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/petrograd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(455145); return false;" >Petrograd</a></span> <span class="odate time_1434584236 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">17 Jun 2015 23:37</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2319320">
									

<p>This doesn't really fit my headcanon, which is why I'm no-voting. The logic of shuffling around so many SCPs between universes is confusing to me unless you accept the central premise, and I'm not quite sold on that, making this more of a proposed-canon-infodump for me.</p>
<p>(Also because it uses Multi-U in a way that's somewhat insidious rather than Bailey-fueled fun, but again, totally a personal preference. Not a real criticism.)</p>
<p>Otherwise, I think it's well written, although it's fairly dry for all that's occurring. It's a bit tragic and blase to see people chatting blithely about layoffs when that's the only interaction we get with them before they're all killed off. (Also, the iPhone thing didn't bother me, because I figured there's no requirement that their 2045 CE matches our CE.)</p>
<p>I did have one question, though. So, it's stated that 2317 has escaped SCP-2317-Prime.<br />
- Does that mean that SCP-2317 has it's own timeline independent of all others, and has just happened to escape into 5463-GOD?<br />
- If so, does this mean the 2317 has permanently breached containment (broken the last chain), and if so, what's keeping it from destroying any other universe?<br />
- Or does each universe have a door to its own 2317?<br />
- Or is the 2317 documentation exclusively referring to a door from 5463-GOD?</p>

							</div>

								
					
