			<div class="content" id="post-content-2319360">
									

<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<blockquote>
<p>This doesn't really fit my headcanon</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Same here, and I'm the author here. This is more of a secondary head-canon for me, since even I admit that it deviates too far from conventional Foundation (hence, me dubbing it a canon).</p>
<blockquote>
<p>it's fairly dry for all that's occurring.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>True, in my older revisions, there were more dynamic interaction scenes initially. By the end of everything, I swapped out almost every interaction with something impersonal:</p>
<ul>
<li>A scene where 173 is being moved out of Site-91 the old fashion way –&gt; an &quot;updated&quot; documentation of it</li>
<li>Dr. Long pleading with Agent Kisch in his office –&gt; email exchange to demonstrate Foundation bureaucracy</li>
<li>An interaction among O5s about 2317 escaping and their more insidious actions –&gt; The Foundation tab</li>
</ul>
<p>And from 2317's page (Level 4 clearance),</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Exploration of the alternate reality (SCP-2317-Prime) is limited</p>
</blockquote>
<p>While we (the readers) know that 2317 is the Devourer entity, Foundation security hid that. I've based the terminology used in the transmission from the Level 4 version.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Does that mean that SCP-2317 has it's own timeline independent of all others</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Maybe pocket dimension, or another previous ruined reality?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>If so, does this mean the 2317 has permanently breached containment (broken the last chain), and if so, what's keeping it from destroying any other universe?</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Well the Devourer is nigh-invincible, if the multiverse is truly infinite, even it will take <em>quite some time</em> before it does real damage. If they try to destroy the roots of the multiverse, that's another story&#8230;</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Or does each universe have a door to its own 2317?</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Maybe? Maybe not? But that's another story.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><em>Please collapse long posts. ~Zyn</em></p>

